Description: Enable Adie's syntax highlighting out of the box
 Adie ships a syntax file but no default colors, so highlighting stays
 invisible until the user configures every style by hand. Install the
 syntax file where Adie looks for it, and provide a default color
 scheme in the system registry, which a user's own settings override.
Author: Logan Russell <me@lrussell.net>
--- a/debian/fox1.6-utils.install
+++ b/debian/fox1.6-utils.install
@@ -7,3 +7,5 @@
 usr/bin/adie-1.6
 usr/bin/calculator-1.6
 usr/bin/shutterbug-1.6
+adie/Adie.stx usr/bin
+debian/foxrc/Adie etc/foxrc
--- a/debian/foxrc/Adie
+++ b/debian/foxrc/Adie
@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@
